    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-20T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-20T02:00:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–2046</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-20T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 20, 1946—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 20—4:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1705. Chou En-lai has requested US plane in order return Nanking October 21.
                    Request has been granted. Sun Fo, President of Legislative Yuan who has been
                    aiding third party efforts in attempt to bring Chou back to Nanking, is
                    confident that it will be possible to work out arrangements for general cease
                    fire order as well as convening of the Three Man Military Committee and Five Man
                    Informal Committee after Chou’s return to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
